  <brief_title>Asthma Severity in Children and Environmental Agents</brief_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>National Institute of Environmental Health Sciences (NIEHS)</agency>
      <agency_class>NIH</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>National Institute of Environmental Health Sciences (NIEHS)</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study measures residential exposures (indoor allergens, mold, nitrogen dioxide,
      nicotine) and relates exposure levels to daily symptoms (wheeze, persistent cough, chest
      tightness, shortness of breath) and medication use, in a population of children with
      physician diagnosed asthma, followed for 12 months.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
